The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks for lesion segmentation in multiple sclerosis, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for identifying lesion changes, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses statistical methods to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for classification, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of information theory to quantify the certainty of lesion changes, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
